HEADWORD: Brasenia
<hw>Brasenia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a magnoliid genus; a genus of
dicotyledonous flowering plants regarded as the most primitive of extant
angiosperms; alternatively, a member of the family
<fam>Nymphaeaceae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Brasenia</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
